1k-utils
A simple and efficient Web development kit。
docs
npm install
npm install 1k-utils

yarn instatll
yarn add 1k-utils

Usage
import { storage } from '1k-utils'
storage('local').set('1', { key: '1' })

babel-plugin-import
[
    "import",
    {
        "libraryName": "1k-utils",
        "camel2DashComponentName": false
    },
    "1k-utils"
]

deserialze.html.title: deserialze
deserialze.html.body:
Types
function deserialze(data: string): Object

Usage
const url = 'https://www.google.cn'
deserialze('a=1&b=2&c[a]=4&arr[0]=4')
deserialze('?&a=1&b=2&c[a]=4&arr[0]=4&?')
deserialze(url + '?key=0&arr[0]=1&arr[1]=2'))
deserialze(url + '?&key=0&arr[0]=1&arr[1]=2'))
// => {a: 1, b: 2, c: {a: 4}, arr: [4]}

getFileAccept.html.title: getFileAccept
getFileAccept.html.body:
Type
interface accept {
    excel: string
    xls: string
    xlsx: string
    word: string
    doc: string
    docx: string
    image: string
    jpg: string
    png: string
    gif: string
    webp: string
    video: string
    mp4: string
    audio: string
    mp3: string
    flac: string
}
function getFileAccept(fileType: T | T[]): string

Usage
getFileAccept('xls')
// => 'application/vnd.ms-excel'
getFileAccept(['xls', 'xlsx'])
getFileAccept('excel')
// => 'application/vnd.ms-excel,application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet'
getFileAccept(['excel', 'image'])
//  => 'application/vnd.ms-excel,application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet,image/jpg, image/jpeg,png,image/png, image/x-png,image/gif, image/webp'
